  "body": "Now that we've established a pattern for passing contexts through to services in #273, let's take advantage of it.\r\n\r\nHere's the chain of events when a user shuts down the beacon node:\r\n1. `BeaconNode` listens for `SIGINT` or `SIGTERM`\r\n2. `BeaconNode` calls `Stop` on all services\r\n3. `Stop` calls `ctx.cancel`\r\n4. goroutines exit\r\n\r\nThe new chain of events should be:\r\n1. `BeaconNode` listens for `SIGINT` or `SIGTERM`\r\n2. `BeaconNode` calls `ctx.cancel` (on its own context)\r\n3. each service receives item from `ctx.Done()` and calls `Stop`\r\n4. goroutines exit\r\n\r\nThe two benefits here are that `Stop` now gets called concurrently, and that subresources of each service can derive its own context from the beacon node context.\r\n\r\nEdit: This should fix the `sharding` package to use the same pattern too.\r\n\r\n ",
